.TH dot 1 "02 FEB 2017" "version 1.0"

.SH COMMAND
.B dot [command] [args] [options]

.SH DESCRIPTION

Dotfile utility tool for managing and running dotfile commands without being in the 
dotfile directory.

.SH COMMANDS

.IP \[bu] 2
.B install [brew|cask|node|zsh]
.I package
.RS
.in +2
Installs the
.B "specified package"
.RB "using the specified package manager and updates"
.RB "the dotfile after successful install."
.RE
.IP \[bu]
.B uninstall [brew|cask|node|zsh]
.I package
.RS
.in +2
Uninstalls the
.B "specified package"
.RB "using the specified package manager and updates"
.RB "the dotfile regardless of whether the uninstall succeeds."
.RE

.SH AUTHOR

Nijiko Yonskai <nijikokun@gmail.com>